\begin{abstract}

We used isospectral transformations from Supersymmetric Quantum Mechanics to get families of dilatons and / or metrics in AdS / QCD models. In particular, we studied the family of dilatons obtained from the equation that describes scalar glueballs on the AdS side in Schr\"odinger form by considering potentials that produce exactly the same spectrum as in models with quadratic dilaton and AdS metric. In addition, we discuss how models based on dilatons in this family can improve AdS / QCD models in order to incorporate chiral symmetry breaking in a good way in this kind of model.

\end{abstract}

