\section{Family of isospectral dilatons}

As we saw in the case of SW models, starting with an AdS metric and a quadratic dilaton it is possible to get a Schr\"odinger-type equation associated with different hadrons on the AdS side. Although it is not a common practice, using the reverse, i.e, starting from a given potential, it is possible to extract a metric and a dilaton which reproduce this potential. This is the base of procedure discussed in this section.

For Schr\"odinger-type equations there are several procedures that make it possible to obtain a family of strictly  isospectral potentials associated with a given potential \cite{AbrahamMoses, Luban:1986iv, Pursey:1986nc, Khare:1989ki, Cooper:1994eh}. As we show in this paper, this technique can be used to get families of metrics and / or dilatons for SW models for a given metric and dilaton. Among different isospectral transformations, in this paper we used a procedure discussed in \cite{Cooper:1994eh}, that considers SUSY QM to get a family of strictly isospectral potentials depending on a parameter.

